<item>
            <title>[HIVE-25976] Cleaner may remove files being accessed from a fetch-task-converted reader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25976</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in a nutshell the following happens:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;query is compiled in fetch-task-converted mode&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;no real execution happens....but the locks are released&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the HS2 is communicating with the client and uses the fetch-task to get the rows - which in this case will directly read files from the table&apos;s directory....&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;client sleeps between reads - so there is ample time for other events...&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;cleaner wakes up and removes some files....&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;in the next read the fetch-task encounters a read error...&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
